—ЩXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/encode_base32hex.mdЩ@37f5e0c897711fa938dd0d83790bf49598a14547d52f3016e3c9535e4edf8b6a·title: encode base32hex‘ЁExamplesЪJEncode a binary value
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[57 6E AD] | encode base32hex
ATNAQ===

```
Encode a string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "hello there" | encode base32hex
D1IMOR3F41Q6GPBICK======

```
Don't apply padding to the output
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "hello there" | encode base32hex --nopad
D1IMOR3F41Q6GPBICK

```
